# Development Workflow

Work in small steps.

Do not generate a large app all at once.

## Before Coding

Before implementing a feature:
- Explain what will be created.
- Mention which files will be added or modified.
- Keep the implementation focused on the current phase.

## Current Phase

The current phase is Phase 1.

Build only:

- Supabase setup.
- Authentication.
- Food inventory CRUD.
- Dashboard.
- Expiring food logic.

Do not build:
- Recipes.
- Meal planning.
- Shopping list.
- Payments.
- AI features.
- Mobile app logic.

Unless explicitly requested.

## Code Quality

Follow these rules:

- Prefer readable code over clever code.
- Use typed models.
- Keep services separate from UI.
- Keep components small.
- Avoid duplicate logic.
- Create reusable utility functions for date calculations.
- Add basic loading and error states.

## Date Logic

Create utility functions for food expiration logic.

Examples:

```ts
isExpired(date: string | null | undefined): boolean
isExpiringSoon(date: string | null | undefined, days?: number): boolean
getExpirationLabel(date: string | null | undefined): string